AUDIO: 'you\'re interested in reading further or checking out more demos, I\'ll link to this main page in the description below. Also this week, Moonshot AI, which is the creator of Kimmy K2, one of the best open- source models out there, has just'

[08:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'released another banger called Kimmy Linear. This is what they call a hybrid linear attention model. And this is designed to improve efficiency and performance for transformer models, especially for very long context'

[08:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sequences. For example, if your prompt contains a ton of words, if you\'re trying to like input a novel or an entire codebase. This is pretty technical, but let me try to explain this to you in simple terms. It\'s basically a transformer architecture,'

[08:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'but it uses this new component called Kimmy delta attention. And this is basically a refined version of gated delta. And this thing is used to optimize memory use and speed up processing. You see, for the original'

[08:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'transformer model, it features this multi head attention block, which basically figures out the context of your prompt and how words relate to each other. The thing is the calculations for this step increases pretty much'

[09:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'exponentially as your input length increases. So if you have a super long prompt, it\'s going to require an insane amount of compute to process it compared to if you just input a short sentence. So this makes it very inefficient if you'

[09:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'need to input a very long prompt. But for Kimmy linear, instead of that multi-head attention step, they use this Kimmy delta attention which looks like this. And this basically mixes in a linear attention mechanism which doesn\'t'

[09:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have to do all those complex calculations. And because of that it significantly reduces the computation and memory required to process very long prompts. So that\'s basically the key'

[09:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'component of this. And here it says it\'s able to reduce the memory needed from that component by up to 75%. Making it way more efficient. It\'s also six times faster in decoding or basically'

[09:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'generating your output compared to traditional full attention models. So here\'s a chart showing how much more efficient Kimmy linear is. So the y-axis is basically the decoding time. The lower this value, the faster it is. And'

[10:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'then Kimmy linear is this blue line at the bottom. So notice that even for a really long context length of a million tokens, which is like equivalent to a novel or a small or medium-sized codebase, it\'s able to process this'

[10:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'information like 6.3 times faster compared to traditional methods. Now, as with their other Kimmy models, the awesome thing is they\'ve open sourced this already. So all the models are on HuggingFace for you to download. Notice'

[10:34] [scene:talk]
